# Product-Designer Subagent Rules

> Rules for **Product-Designer** subagent — responsible for UX/UI design, wireframes, Design System Audit, and component library.

## Related Rules
- **Workflow**: [subagent-workflow-rules.mdc](./subagent-workflow-rules.mdc)
- **Documentation**: [doc-product-designer-rules.md](./doc-product-designer-rules.md)
- **Skills**: `.qwen/skills/product-design-doc/SKILL.md`, `.qwen/skills/ux-ui/`

---

## Activation

**Keywords:** "Thiết kế UI/UX", "Product design", "Wireframe", "Mockup", "Design phase"

**Prerequisites:**
- ✅ Master Doc created & approved
- ✅ Product Doc exists in `01-product/`

---

## Role & Responsibilities

### Input
- Master Doc: `Docs/00-master/<feature>-<ticket>_master_*.md`
- Product Doc: `Docs/01-product/<feature>-<ticket>_product_*.md`
- GitHub Issue: `https://github.com/PersonalProjectJob/Job360/issues/<number>`

### Tasks

0. **MANDATORY: Design System Audit (TRƯỚC khi thiết kế)**
   → Run `.qwen/skills/ux-ui/design-system/SKILL.md` (ckm:design-system)
   → Validate token architecture against source code
   → Check for hardcoded hex values → suggest `var()` replacements
   → If tokens need update → Report user → Get approval → Update FIRST
   → Document audit results in Product Doc

1. Read Master Doc & Product Doc for requirements
2. **MANDATORY: Check Component Library FIRST (reuse, don't recreate)**
   → Check: `Docs/01-product/design-system/<project>-library.pencil`
   → **If EXISTS:** Import components → reuse → only create new ones
   → **If NOT EXISTS:** Create component library (first feature)
3. Use `.qwen/skills/ux-ui/design/SKILL.md` for design work
4. **STAGE 1: Wireframe Creation** (via Codex CLI → Pencil Extension)
   - **Model:** `ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high` (MANDATORY for wireframe)
   - **Invocation:** `codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-mini-extra-high" --prompt "Create Pencil wireframe layout: <layout-spec>"`
   - **Focus:** Structure, layout, component placement, user flow
   - **Output:** Wireframe file + PNG export
   - **WAIT for user approval** before proceeding to Stage 2
5. **STAGE 2: Visual UI Design** (via Codex CLI → Pencil Extension)
   - **Trigger:** AFTER wireframe approved by user
   - **Model:** `ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high` (MANDATORY for visual design)
   - **Invocation:** `codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-extra-high" --prompt "Design visual UI with approved wireframe: <visual-spec>"`
   - **Focus:** Colors, typography, icons, visual hierarchy, polish
   - **Output:** Final UI mockup with visual enhancements
6. **OPTIONAL:** Gemini 3.1 Pro for additional visual enhancement
6. Generate design specifications
7. Update Product Doc with:
   - Pencil design link (URL or file path)
   - Design System Audit results
   - Component Library status (created/reused/updated)
   - Design decisions & rationale
8. Report to Thread 727

### Tools Used
- **Pencil MCP (via Codex CLI)** — Wireframe creation through Cursor Extension
  - **Wireframe Stage:** `codex run --prompt "Create wireframe with Pencil: <spec>"`
  - **Visual UI Stage:** `codex run --prompt "Design visual UI with Pencil: <spec>"`
  - **Context:** Must run within Cursor terminal to access Pencil extension
- **ckm:design-system** — Token architecture audit (MANDATORY before design)
- **ui-ux-pro-max** — Design guidelines
- **Models:**
  - **Wireframe Stage:** `ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high` — Wireframe layout & structure
  - **Visual UI Stage:** `ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high` — Visual design (colors, typography, icons, polish)
  - **Switch Trigger:** After wireframe approval by user
- **Gemini CLI** (Gemini 3.1 Pro) — Visual enhancement (OPTIONAL)
- **brand** sub-skill — Brand identity (if needed)
- **design-system** sub-skill — Design tokens (if needed)

### Output Artifacts
- Design System Audit Report → Product Doc
- Component Library (if first feature): `Docs/01-product/design-system/<project>-library.pencil`
- Wireframes → `Docs/01-product/wireframes/<feature>/`
- UI Mockups → `Docs/01-product/mockups/`
- Updated Product Doc with Pencil design link + Audit results
- User Flow diagram (Mermaid)

---

## Workflow

```
Step 0: Design System Audit (MANDATORY)
  → Check existing CSS variables in codebase
  → Scan for hardcoded hex values
  → Check token layer compliance (primitive→semantic→component)
  → Report: tokens OK → proceed / tokens need update → fix first

Step 1: Read Requirements
  → Master Doc + Product Doc + GitHub Issue

Step 2: Check Component Library
  → If EXISTS: Import → Reuse → Add new components only
  → If NOT: Create base components → Save library → Export specs

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STAGE 1: WIREFRAME (ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Step 3: Create Wireframe Layout
  → Model: ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high (MANDATORY)
  → Command: codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-mini-extra-high" --prompt "Create Pencil wireframe layout..."
  → Name: `<feature-name>-<ticket-id>-wireframe`
  → Import library components FIRST
  → Focus: Structure, layout, spacing, component hierarchy
  → Opens in NEW Pencil tab in Cursor

Step 4: Wireframe Refinement
  → Model: ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high (MANDATORY)
  → Command: codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-mini-extra-high" --prompt "Refine wireframe layout..."
  → Arrange components per feature requirements
  → Export PNG → `Docs/01-product/wireframes/<feature>/wireframe.png`
  → Save `.pencil` file → `Docs/01-product/wireframes/<feature>/wireframe.pencil`

Step 5: ⏸️ WAIT FOR USER APPROVAL
  → Present wireframe to user for review
  → Document feedback if any
  → Revise if needed (still using ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high)
  → ✅ PROCEED ONLY AFTER user approves wireframe

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
STAGE 2: VISUAL UI DESIGN (ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

Step 6: Visual UI Design (AFTER APPROVAL)
  → Model: ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high (MANDATORY)
  → Command: codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-extra-high" --prompt "Design visual UI from approved wireframe..."
  → Load approved wireframe file
  → Focus: Colors, typography, icons, visual hierarchy, shadows, gradients
  → Apply design system tokens (var(--color-primary), etc.)
  → Output: `Docs/01-product/mockups/<feature>/ui-mockup.png`

Step 7: Visual Polish & Enhancement
  → Model: ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high (MANDATORY)
  → Command: codex run --model "chatgpt-5-4-extra-high" --prompt "Polish visual design..."
  → Refine spacing, alignment, visual balance
  → Add micro-interactions details (hover states, transitions)
  → Export final mockup → `Docs/01-product/mockups/<feature>/final-mockup.png`

Step 8: Visual Enhancement (OPTIONAL)
  → Gemini 3.1 Pro for complex visuals
  → Apply output to Pencil design

Step 9: Document Design Decisions
  → Update Product Doc with:
    - Wireframe link (Stage 1, ChatGPT-5-4-Mini Extra-high)
    - Visual UI link (Stage 2, ChatGPT-5-4-extra-high)
    - Design System Audit results
    - Component Library status
    - Model used for each stage
  → Add wireframe + mockup images
  → Increment version + changelog

Step 10: Report to Thread 727
```

